Been working on some new #Dimensional glass this week and they seem to be evolving with a mind of their own 🤯 The depth and beauty of this glass is that it never ceases to amaze me... with every piece constructed I’m pulled deeper into a fractalized world of color and light: one side of the Tesseract core is showing heavy Primary spectrum, when flipped to the other side a whole #Technicolor spectrums appears! 🌈⚡️💫✨
💎💎💎
SWIPE LEFT for detail shots
This “DiMensional Tetrahedron Core” features my #DimensionalGlass tech all under a symmetrical #freehandfaceted and polished cut for some beautiful color refraction and optics and measures an equal 33mm X 33m X 33m...
